Cell.Text: G|Go on in. Jarl Ulfric likes to welcome all the new recruits personally.

Node.Caption: MQ102BGuardBlockingTopic: I'm here to join up with the Stormcloaks.

Cell.Text: You won't take me because I'm an Argonian?
<<Shared>> Never said that. Just that we don't get many of you wanting to join, that's all.
You won't take me because I'm a Khajiit?
<<Shared>> Never said that. Just that we don't get many of you wanting to join, that's all.
You won't take me because I'm an elf?
<<Shared>> Never said that. Just that we don't get many of you wanting to join, that's all.
We'd be glad to have you, whatever color you happen to be, as long as you're willing to pledge your blood and honor for Skyrim's freedom.
"...Jarl of Windhelm and true High King of Skyrim."

Node.Caption: MQ102BStormcloakOath1: I do swear my blood and honor to the service of Ulfric Stormcloak...

Cell.Text: "As Talos is my witness, may this oath bind me to death and beyond..."

Node.Caption: MQ102BStormcloakOath2: ...Jarl of Windhelm and true High King of Skyrim.

Cell.Text: "... even to my lord as to my fellow brothers and sisters in arms."

Cell.Text: [S] Now you're one of us. | Which means you get to tag along on a little trip with me.

Node.Caption: MQ102BStormcloakOath4: All hail the Stormcloaks, the true sons and daughters of Skyrim!

Cell.Text: Changed your mind? You ready to pledge your blood and honor for Skyrim's freedom?

Node.Caption: MQ102GalmarJoinTopic: I want to join up with the Sons of Skyrim.

Cell.Text: Now, are you sure you're ready to pledge your blood and honor for Skyrim's freedom?

Node.Caption: MQ102GalmarIntroNormal: I want to join the Stormcloaks.

Cell.Text: Hold on there. I didn't mean to be insulting. Just that we don't get many of your kind wanting to join is all.

Node.Caption: MQ102GalmarIntroNo: I'm not sure I want to join after all.

Cell.Text: [S] Well now, I don't know. We don't have many lizards in our ranks.
[S] Well now, I don't know. We don't have many cats in our ranks.
[S] Well now, I don't know. We don't have many elves in our ranks. They tend to side with the Empire.
[S] We're always glad to welcome another true son of Skyrim to our ranks. Well, "daughter" in your case, but that's no matter here.
[S] We're always glad to welcome another true son of Skyrim to our ranks.

[S] You really want to join our cause? Most of you foreigners don't seem to give a damn about Skyrim's oppression. | I guess being dragged to the headsman's block for no reason opened your eyes to the truth about the Empire, eh?
G|It's Jarl Ulfric you want. He'll decide if you're worthy to join our ranks.
G|We're not done here.

G|Don't take too long figuring it out. Might mistake your hesitation for Imperial sympathies. | Come back when you're committed to the cause, or go join the Legion. They're taking anyone with a pulse these days.

Node.Caption: CW01BGalmarGreetGoodbye: I need to think it over.
